# 🐦 BirdVision

This is a bird detection system I built using AI.
It can detect and identify birds from **images, videos, and live camera feed**.

Basically:

* YOLO → finds the bird
* ResNet → tells what bird it is

And it shows the name in:

* English
* Sinhala

---

## 🔥 What it can do

* Detect birds from images
* Process videos frame-by-frame
* Run real-time detection using webcam
* Show bird name + confidence
* Show Sinhala translation

---

## 🧠 How it works (simple)

1. YOLOv8 detects the bird location
2. That region is cropped
3. ResNet50 classifies the bird
4. Output is drawn on screen

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
BirdVision/
│
├── main.py        # image + video detection
├── live.py        # live camera detection
│
├── models/
│   ├── best.pt
│   ├── bird_resnet50.pth
│   ├── classes.json
│   ├── sinhala_map.json
│   └── species_info.json
│
├── fonts/
│   └── NotoSansSinhala-Regular.ttf
```

---

## ⚙️ How to run

### 1. Clone repo

```
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/BirdVision.git
cd BirdVision
```

---

### 2. Setup environment

```
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
```

---

### 3. Install dependencies

```
pip install ultralytics opencv-python pillow torch torchvision
```

---

### 4. Run it

#### Image / Video

```
python main.py
```

#### Live Camera

```
python live.py
```

Press **Q** to quit live feed.

---

## 🧪 Trained Birds

Currently trained on:

* Green Parrot
* Black Hooded Oriole
* House Sparrow
* White Throated Kingfisher
* (more can be added)

---

## ⚠️ Notes

* Make sure models are inside `models/`
* Make sure Sinhala font is inside `fonts/`
* Camera index might change depending on your device

